<seg id="750">& dot; algorithm, the standard for directional graphs. it produces hierarchical or layered representations of aligned graphs. the algorithm sets the edges in the same direction (from top to bottom or from left to right) and then attempts to produce as short edges as possible and as few edge overlaps as possible.</seg>
