<seg id="1042">If a picture is rendered with only one beam per pixel, different errors can occur. these images often have a Moiré pattern or step effects in curves and lines, and sometimes details are not displayed if they are smaller than a pixel. this effect is called aliasing.</seg>
<seg id="1043">& Povray; uses a technique called anti-aliasing to reduce the impact of these errors. generally, pictures with this property look better.</seg>
<seg id="1044">When you switch on anti-aliasing, calculates and connects & Povray; more than one beam per pixel. this technique is called super-sampling.</seg>
<seg id="1045">& Povray; supports two methods of super-sampling. as a standard, an adaptive, non-recursive method; adaptive because the super-sampling integrates the neighbouring pixels. the second method is adaptive-recursive; recursively because each pixel is split up again and again and adaptively because the recursion depth depends on calculated color values.</seg>
<seg id="1046">If you choose the first method, POV-Ray tracks a beam of each pixel. if the difference between the color values exceeds the specified threshold, then both pixels are processed by tracking a certain additional number of pixels with super-sampling. if you set the depth value to 4, a grid of 5 then 5x5 (25) additional rays each pixel.</seg>
<seg id="1047">The difference between two pixels is calculated as follows: R 1, g 1 and b 1 are the values for red, green and blue of the first pixel, r 2, g 2 and b 2 are the values for red, green and blue of the second pixel. the difference is then:</seg>
<seg id="1048">Diff = abs (r 1 -r 2) + abs (g 1 -g 2) + abs (b 1 -g 2)</seg>
<seg id="1049">The recursive method starts with 4 beams per pixel. if the difference between the color values exceeds the given threshold, then the pixel is divided into 4 sub-pixel, which are further pursued and checked for further subdivision. the maximum depth of the recursion can be adjusted with the depth value.</seg>
<seg id="1050">Another option to reduce the aliasing effect is the creation of noise for the beam process called Jittering. if you turn on jittering, changing & Povray; the rays are around a tiny amount to avoid regular patterns.</seg>
